Text:
@lolzob

Integrated March 2013? When installed it wants to update over 100 updates (several hundreds of megabytes), and some of the dates of those updates goes back in 2011 (!). And Internet Explorer 8.0 comes with it, not 10.0 as the description says. I'm not ungrateful, as this is "free", but don't say it's "march 2013" when it's clearly not.

Do not download this if you expect it to be a fully updated (march 2013) Windows 7 ISO.

@lolzob: I did check it. I would get screenshots if I could with a virtual machine but I installed another release instead as I was in a hurry. I was so glad that I could choose from Home Premium, Professional and Ultimate, so when I saw Professional I took that instead and took for granted that the updates was deployed to all versions, which you later told to slackeritguy.

Even though you did deploy to all the versions, it seems it failed, because there were lots of entries of errors and warnings in Event Viewer which seemed to be related to failed integrations (extractions?) of updates.

I'm sorry if I sounded a bit harsh, but like I said I was in a hurry at the time so it was a bit disappointing with over 100 updates on the Professional version. I hope you can understand that. I meant no offence. :)

@slackeritguy: Exactly, then I didn't imagine things.
